



Sir
[31 August 1775]



I am Vary Sorey that thare was aney Misunder Standing in the mesage that your Eadeyeon Braught me Respecting the Signal that I was to mack on Powder Horn Hill[.] I under Stood By him that when Aney movement By See or Land By the
[389]
Regular trupes was mad that was Lickley that thay ware a Bout to Land I was to give the Signal on Said hill[.]1 I have in Closed the Remarckes.2 I am your Exelencey most Humble Servent

Richd Dodge Capt.

